Job functions:
Lead and oversee regional sourcing teams, manage the performance and compliance to policy and procedure;
Manage sourcing team to well collaborate with counterpart across the Group to identify the material, component and product needs;
Formulate and responsible for departmental goals and strategies that align with company goads
Monitor the vendor’s performance to ensure the fulfillment of safety,  quality, pricing, delivery schedules, commercial terms and other requirements  
Develop and maintain the long term partnership with vendors, manage vendor selection and evaluation, and improvement initiatives;
Formulate and execute the contract management and policy, and effective negotiate prices
Analysis and share with the management in regular basis the updated market information and price trend;
Develop and drive the strategic programs such as cost saving initiative, continuous improvement projects and monitor the execution and goals achievements;
Provide quick response and implement effective plans and solutions to meet the emerging needs
Networking with target suppliers, and industry practitioners
Perform ad hoc assignment by management
Requirements:
Diploma or above in Procurement, Purchasing, Materials Management, Supply Chain, or related disciplines;
Over 8 years strategic procurement and sourcing, development of material supplier / sub-contractor, and project management experience preferably gained from multinational or sizeable manufacturing companies with minimum 5 years in managerial position;
Solid experience in material sourcing of Printing / Paper Products / Toys & Gifts Industry would be an advantage;
Global sourcing experience and strong experience in managing China vendors
Strong people management skill and influencing skill;
Excellent analytical, communication & negotiation skills;
Result-oriented, team player
Good command of written and spoken English, and Chinese/Mandarin;
Travel to Asian countries is required
Candidates with more experience will be considered as Procurement Director
Application:
Please send your CV, existing salary & expected salary in WORD format to ghr  @ qpp.com
All personal information collected will be kept for employment related purposes only.

